<node CREATED="1400677618859" ID="ID_446286066" MODIFIED="1400677622664" POSITION="right" TEXT="Deadlines">
<node CREATED="1400678045024" MODIFIED="1400678045024">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; margin-right: 0px; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; margin-top: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin-left: 0px; font-style: normal; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">Yes, a tight deadline indeed, though Vonu is very keen to have us involved so we might be able to squeeze a bit more time if needed. Just to confirm: if I can&#8217;t make the conference due to moving house, are you still able to go in my place to present? Dates are 11-12 August. My travel will get paid from UBDC I think but your travel could be funded by AQMEN or the School. Maybe you could submit an application to the School conference budget? I copy below the abstract we submitted.</font></span>
    </p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; margin-right: 0px; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; margin-top: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin-left: 0px; font-style: normal; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">&#160;</font></span>
    </p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; margin-right: 0px; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; margin-top: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin-left: 0px; font-style: normal; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">So, we have until 15<sup>th</sup></font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)">July to write a conference paper. Here&#8217;s the plan:</span></font>
    </p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; margin-right: 0px; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; margin-top: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin-left: 0px; font-style: normal; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">&#160;</font></span>
    </p>
    <p style="letter-spacing: normal; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <b><span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">1.</font></span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">wb 12<sup>th</sup></font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)">May:</span></font></b>
    </p>
    <p style="letter-spacing: normal; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; margin-left: 72pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">a.</font></span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font><b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">Gwilym</font></span></b><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)">to work on the language data using the same textual categorisation as Oates &amp; Pryce. This will initially be done at dwelling level. We will need to decide whether to aggregate this up to output area or datazone. I will do both, but I propose we initially work with datazones.</span></font>
    </p>
    <p style="letter-spacing: normal; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; margin-left: 72pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">b.</font></span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font><b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">Jon</font></span></b><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)">to email Nema to ask what R package she used to do the social network analysis (or perhaps you can work this out from Nema&#8217;s slides?).</span></font>
    </p>
    <p style="letter-spacing: normal; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">2.</font></span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font><b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">wb 19<sup>th</sup></font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)">May:</span></font></b>
    </p>
    <p style="letter-spacing: normal; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; margin-left: 72pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">a.</font></span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font><b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">Jon</font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font></b><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)">to take Gwilym&#8217;s data and create a social network for 2011. Do some initial measures of network structure. Then test whether distance between nodes (i.e. datazone centroids) affects the probability of their being a link between nodes.</span></font>
    </p>
    <p style="letter-spacing: normal; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; margin-left: 72pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">b.</font></span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font><b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">Jon</font></span></b><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)">to add in node variables from SNS on ethnicity and demography</span></font>
    </p>
    <p style="letter-spacing: normal; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; margin-left: 72pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">c.</font></span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font><b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">Gwilym</font></span></b><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)">draft paper structure and initial literature review.</span></font>
    </p>
    <p style="letter-spacing: normal; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <b><span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">3.</font></span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">Wb 26<sup>th</sup></font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)">May:</span></font></b>
    </p>
    <p style="letter-spacing: normal; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; margin-left: 72pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">a.</font></span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">Jon to test for homophily in ethnicity in 2011 and repeat the analysis for 2001.</font></span>
    </p>
    <p style="letter-spacing: normal; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; margin-left: 72pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">b.</font></span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">Jon to re-run the analysis using % change between 2001 and 2011. i.e. the network now becomes a dynamic one, where we use % change in language as the basis for links between datazones, and the covariates are in % change also (% change in ethnicity). Compute homophily measures.</font></span>
    </p>
    <p style="letter-spacing: normal; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">4.</font></span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">wb 2<sup>nd</sup></font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)">June:</span></font>
    </p>
    <p style="letter-spacing: normal; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; margin-left: 72pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">a.</font></span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font></span><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="7pt" face="Times New Roman"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&#160;</span></font><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">Gwilym to write up the results and the rest of the paper.</font></span>
    </p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; margin-right: 0px; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; margin-top: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin-left: 0px; font-style: normal; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">&#160;</font></span>
    </p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; margin-right: 0px; font-size: 13px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; text-align: start; font-weight: normal; font-variant: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-indent: 0px; line-height: normal; word-spacing: 0px; margin-top: 0px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin-left: 0px; font-style: normal; color: rgb(34, 34, 34)">
      <span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 73, 125)"><font color="rgb(31, 73, 125)" size="11pt" face="Calibri, sans-serif">This will give us the rest of June to revise and update the paper. What do you think? The attached may be of some use in terms of providing an example of similar analysis based on house price movements.</font></span>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
